        "titre": "PERSONA",
        "cineaste": "BERGMAN",
        "annee": 1966
      }
    ],
    "declaration": "First of all, let me start out by saying that my taste in all things cinema is not strictly constrained by conventional distinctions along the line of genre: while drama and experimental films, indeed, make up most of my best ever chart, I can easily find beauty in a comedy or in a western. The reason I'm still a voracious cinephile is a yearning for the absolute image: a representation that goes beyond the subjective point of view and allows me to see the world with a new eye that is able to grasp the whole. Human vision is ordinarily atomistic, an easy prey to the obtuse whims of the moment. The task of cinema, as I understand it, is to open up perception to objective thought and to an ethical commitment to truth, so that man may escape the prison of his own ego and attain a vision which is at the same time rational and ecstatic.",
